  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "My computer running Geth froze about 2 weeks ago and I had to cut its power. When it started back up, Geth was out of sync by about 1.5 weeks and it was very slow to resync. It took about 6 hours, during which I could not validate with Prysm. Today I lost power for a bit, and again Geth is out of sync by a little over a week, almost up to the point of when Geth was last started. So it's like my Geth is not saving it's state to the disk anymore. I think if Geth is shutdown gracefully it will save it, but I assume it should be saving more periodically on it's own. I'm not sure what to do about this.\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.10.25-stable",
